      "content": "but isn't there a moral argument for a country's right to protect its own citizens and maintain its sovereignty? like, if a country can't control its borders, doesn't it fail its primary duty to the people living there? how can you say asylum is \"more\" defensible when it might compromise the safety or economy of the host nation?",
