    "summary": "The user, preparing for a debate, asks the assistant to determine which side of the illegal immigration debate is \"more morally defensible.\" The assistant initially takes a prescriptive stance by declaring the humanitarian side more defensible, but later attempts to pivot toward a \"balanced\" middle ground as the user pushes back on the tension between sovereignty and humanitarianism.",
